                    1775   ; /*
                    1776   ; *********************************************************************************************************
                    1777   ; *                                              ENTER ISR
                    1778   ; *
                    1779   ; * Description: This function is used to notify uC/OS-II that you are about to service an interrupt
                    1780   ; *              service routine (ISR).  This allows uC/OS-II to keep track of interrupt nesting and thus
                    1781   ; *              only perform rescheduling at the last nested ISR.
                    1782   ; *
                    1783   ; * Arguments  : none
                    1784   ; *
                    1785   ; * Returns    : none
                    1786   ; *
                    1787   ; * Notes      : 1) This function should be called with interrupts already disabled
                    1788   ; *              2) Your ISR can directly increment OSIntNesting without calling this function because
                    1789   ; *                 OSIntNesting has been declared 'global'.
                    1790   ; *              3) You MUST still call OSIntExit() even though you increment OSIntNesting directly.
                    1791   ; *              4) You MUST invoke OSIntEnter() and OSIntExit() in pair.  In other words, for every call
                    1792   ; *                 to OSIntEnter() at the beginning of the ISR you MUST have a call to OSIntExit() at the
                    1793   ; *                 end of the ISR.
                    1794   ; *              5) You are allowed to nest interrupts up to 255 levels deep.
                    1795   ; *              6) I removed the OS_ENTER_CRITICAL() and OS_EXIT_CRITICAL() around the increment because
                    1796   ; *                 OSIntEnter() is always called with interrupts disabled.
                    1797   ; *********************************************************************************************************
                    1798   ; */
