                    3534   ; *                 and then disabling interrupts didn't allow the processor enough time to have interrupts
                    3535   ; *                 enabled before they were disabled again.  uC/OS-II would thus never recognize
                    3536   ; *                 interrupts.
                    3537   ; *              2) This hook has been added to allow you to do such things as STOP the CPU to conserve
                    3538   ; *                 power.
