                    4366   ; /*
                    4367   ; *********************************************************************************************************
                    4368   ; *                                        CREATE AN EVENT FLAG
                    4369   ; *
                    4370   ; * Description: This function is called to create an event flag group.
                    4371   ; *
                    4372   ; * Arguments  : flags         Contains the initial value to store in the event flag group.
                    4373   ; *
                    4374   ; *              perr          is a pointer to an error code which will be returned to your application:
                    4375   ; *                               OS_ERR_NONE               if the call was successful.
                    4376   ; *                               OS_ERR_CREATE_ISR         if you attempted to create an Event Flag from an
                    4377   ; *                                                         ISR.
                    4378   ; *                               OS_ERR_FLAG_GRP_DEPLETED  if there are no more event flag groups
                    4379   ; *
                    4380   ; * Returns    : A pointer to an event flag group or a NULL pointer if no more groups are available.
                    4381   ; *
                    4382   ; * Called from: Task ONLY
