                    9558   ; *
                    9559   ; * Returns    : != (void *)0  is the message in the queue if one is available.  The message is removed
                    9560   ; *                            from the so the next time OSQAccept() is called, the queue will contain
                    9561   ; *                            one less entry.
                    9562   ; *              == (void *)0  if you received a NULL pointer message
