                    12568   ; *********************************************************************************************************
                    12569   ; *                                            CREATE A TASK
                    12570   ; *
                    12571   ; * Description: This function is used to have uC/OS-II manage the execution of a task.  Tasks can either
                    12572   ; *              be created prior to the start of multitasking or by a running task.  A task cannot be
                    12573   ; *              created by an ISR.
                    12574   ; *
                    12575   ; * Arguments  : task     is a pointer to the task's code
                    12576   ; *
                    12577   ; *              p_arg    is a pointer to an optional data area which can be used to pass parameters to
                    12578   ; *                       the task when the task first executes.  Where the task is concerned it thinks
                    12579   ; *                       it was invoked and passed the argument 'p_arg' as follows:
                    12580   ; *
                    12581   ; *                           void Task (void *p_arg)
                    12582   ; *                           {
                    12583   ; *                               for (;;) {
                    12584   ; *                                   Task code;
                    12585   ; *                               }
                    12586   ; *                           }
                    12587   ; *
                    12588   ; *              ptos     is a pointer to the task's top of stack.  If the configuration constant
                    12589   ; *                       OS_STK_GROWTH is set to 1, the stack is assumed to grow downward (i.e. from high
                    12590   ; *                       memory to low memory).  'pstk' will thus point to the highest (valid) memory
                    12591   ; *                       location of the stack.  If OS_STK_GROWTH is set to 0, 'pstk' will point to the
                    12592   ; *                       lowest memory location of the stack and the stack will grow with increasing
                    12593   ; *                       memory locations.
                    12594   ; *
                    12595   ; *              prio     is the task's priority.  A unique priority MUST be assigned to each task and the
                    12596   ; *                       lower the number, the higher the priority.
                    12597   ; *
                    12598   ; * Returns    : OS_ERR_NONE                      if the function was successful.
                    12599   ; *              OS_ERR_PRIO_EXIST                if the task priority already exist
                    12600   ; *                                               (each task MUST have a unique priority).
                    12601   ; *              OS_ERR_PRIO_INVALID              if the priority you specify is higher that the maximum
                    12602   ; *                                               allowed (i.e. >= OS_LOWEST_PRIO)
                    12603   ; *              OS_ERR_TASK_CREATE_ISR           if you tried to create a task from an ISR.
                    12604   ; *              OS_ERR_ILLEGAL_CREATE_RUN_TIME   if you tried to create a task after safety critical
                    12605   ; *                                               operation started.
                    12606   ; *********************************************************************************************************
                    12607   ; */
