                    14297   ; *
                    14298   ; * Description: This function is called to change the current value of a task register.  Task registers
                    14299   ; *              are application specific and can be used to store task specific values such as 'error
                    14300   ; *              numbers' (i.e. errno), statistics, etc.  Each task register can hold a 32-bit value.
                    14301   ; *
                    14302   ; * Arguments  : prio      is the priority of the task you want to set the task register for.  If you
                    14303   ; *                        specify OS_PRIO_SELF then the task register of the current task will be obtained.
                    14304   ; *
